<br>
You pretty much should single pull until 54, but I've heard of people able to use Pillar of Frost and be able to pull it off even with the resists.<br>
<br>
For single pulling you just tag it with staff, run down to the beach, BoF/Atol's it, and kite it down with Draught of Fire. The otters will ignore everything so just feel free to use the extent of the beach. I could usually get 2 kills in doign this before getting too low on mana (roughly 2 bub of mana per kill)<br>
<br>
For quadding, almost the same thing, scout out 4 blue wyverns, watch for the cobalt drakes to make sure you dont run by them. Then pull a drive-by fluxing with your staff and tag all 4 and bring them to the beach. Play cowboy and round'em up then BoF/Atol's them, then Pillar of Lightning them to death. This look about 3 bubbles of mana.<br>
<br>
JBoots are almost a must here, and Levitate makes sure you dont embarass yourself and die from falling damage trying to run to the beach.<br>
<br>
Just watch out for those Cobalt Drakes, they have a HUGE radius 495 dmg + 1 dispell AoE. This really makes everyone who's in CS mad if you do it. If they argo though, simply drag it down to the middle otter camp (with the chief in it) and wait until the stupid drake AoE's again and argos the whole friggin otter camp, laugh at the drake, and med up.<br>
<br>
Another mob to watch for is Yvolcarn, it appears he is almost always up, in a random spot where a Wyvern can normally spawn. Seems if he's up, it's only 1 of him. He is a level 52 (can summon) drake that will assist Wyverns, he also gives a CoV faction hit if you kill him. So scout out before you pull and make sure he's not in your path.<br>
<br>
G'luck and happy leveling<br>
